    "body": "### Neovim version (nvim -v)\r\n\r\nv0.8.0-dev+377-gae02c02f1\r\n\r\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\r\n\r\nNo\r\n\r\n### Operating system/version\r\n\r\nArch Linux\r\n\r\n### Terminal name/version\r\n\r\nkitty 0.25.1\r\n\r\n### $TERM environment variable\r\n\r\nxterm-kitty\r\n\r\n### Installation\r\n\r\nbuild from repo\r\n\r\n### How to reproduce the issue\r\n\r\n1. Run `nvim --clean`\r\n2. Source the following file:\r\n```vim\r\nimap <expr> <F2> [timer_start(0, { _ -> execute(\"throw 'x'\", \"\") }), ''][-1]\r\ninoremap <F2>a foo\r\n```\r\n3. Type `i<F2>`\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nAn error is thrown after the `<F2>a` mapping times out and the `<F2>` mapping is triggered.\r\n\r\n### Actual behavior\r\n\r\nNo error is thrown until the next key after the `<F2>` is pressed.",
